There were 24 pheasants at the start. Of these 16 were shot dead, 1 was wounded in the wing, and 7 got away but “how many still remained?” Now the poor bird that was wounded in the wing, though unable to fly, was very active in its painful struggles to run away. The answer is, therefore, that the 16 birds that were shot dead “still remained,” or “remained still.”

